  "prompt": "What are the steps to put my car in Ola Cab services?",
  "response": "To register your car with Ola Cab services, follow these general steps:\n\n1. Check Eligibility\n- Meet Ola's vehicle requirements (age, model, condition)\n- Have valid vehicle documents\n- Possess a valid driver's license\n\n2. Online Registration\n- Visit Ola's official website or download Ola Driver app\n- Create an account\n- Fill in personal and vehicle details\n\n3. Document Submission\n- Upload required documents:\n- Vehicle registration certificate\n- Insurance\n- Driving license\n- Pollution certificate\n- Address proof\n- Passport-size photograph\n\n4. Vehicle Inspection\n- Ola will schedule a physical vehicle inspection\n- Verify vehicle condition and documents\n- Check car's mechanical fitness\n\n5. Background Verification\n- Submit additional documents\n- Undergo background check\n- Verify driver's credentials\n\n6. Agreement and Training\n- Sign partnership agreement\n- Attend Ola's driver orientation/training\n- Understand company policies\n\n7. Activation\n- Complete all formalities\n- Receive driver partner ID\n- Start earning through Ola platform\n\nNote: Specific requirements might vary by city and region. Check Ola's official website or contact their customer support for precise, current details.",
